narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a great deal about the EV industry, the regulatory process in the utilities industry, and public policy engagement more generally.

narratives.question_text: How well did the knowledge, skills, and insights gained in this class align with your expectations?
comments: Very well, learnt much more than I though I would!
Very well - this course exceeded my expectations and was a tremendous opportunity to work with a leading organization in AEE.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of the course and how could it be improved?
comments: A little bit more structure and clearer expectations would have been helpful.

We took a while in the beginning to sort out the projects, but other than that no complaints. The strengths of the course are the diversity of project options, the access to AEE/other leading organizations, and the ability to work with Dan Utech, who is a leading public policy thinker in this space.

narratives.question_text: What advice would you give to a student considering taking this class?
comments: Be prepared to work with ambiguous challenges and mentally tiring work yet ultimately very rewarding!!
Make sure you screen the projects beforehand, know if one fits your interests.
